  "body": "When creating an instance of `c1` with the following code, the constructor automatically creates an instance of `c2`. For debugging purposes it would be extremely helpful if this nested instance `myC2` would be shown in the contracts tab and I could, e.g. see its address and call its functions:\r\n```\r\ncontract c1 {\r\n    c2 myC2;\r\n    function c1() {\r\n        myC2 = new c2();\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    function getC1() constant returns (uint) {\r\n        return 1;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract c2 {\r\n    function getC2() constant returns (uint) {\r\n        return 2;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
